                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> That sucks :/ Had it happen to me long long ago. Never do trades with unguilded toons unless you already know them. If they're in a guild, it's much more likely you can trust them. Not entirely, but at least then there is always their guild you can petition to. While that may not get your items back, it could ruin their reputation more than if they were unguilded. Better yet if they're in a reputable guild.<br /><br />That goes for any sort of combine. Also search the 200+ research post here on the boards. Most, if not all, listed there are most likely fairly trustworthy. Still, if they're in a guild you have more of a safety margin.</span id="msg"></font></td>
